  "severity": "Important",
  "description": "MariaDB is a multi-user, multi-threaded SQL database server that is binary compatible with MySQL. \n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* mariadb: MariaDB Server: Arbitrary code execution via wsrep_notify_cmd (CVE-2026-49261)\n\nBug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s):\n\n* [Rocky Linux9][tracker] Rebase Galera to 26.4.27 MariaDB:10.11 (JIRA:Rocky Linux-140363)\n\n* Rebase MariaDB 10.11 to 10.11.18 in Rocky Linux9 (JIRA:Rocky Linux-183087)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
